# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# Tutorial 1 -- potential comparison (solution only)
# Same calculation as minimize.lmp but with the Mendelev Al EAM potential
# in Finnis-Sinclair file format (eam/fs). For a single element this is the
# same EAM model as eam/alloy, only the file format differs.

units metal
dimension 3
boundary p p p
atom_style atomic

lattice fcc 4.05 origin 0.25 0.25 0.25
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 4.05 4.05 4.05
region box block 0 4 0 4 0 4
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (16.2 16.2 16.2)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 256 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (16.2 16.2 16.2)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.000 seconds

pair_style eam/fs
pair_coeff * * Al_mm.eam.fs Al
Reading eam/fs potential file Al_mm.eam.fs with DATE: 2007-06-11

thermo 10
thermo_style custom step pe press lx

fix relax all box/relax iso 0.0 vmax 0.001
min_style cg
minimize 1.0e-12 1.0e-12 10000 100000
